OUTLINE TERMS OF REFERENCE FOR CONSULTANTS 

A.  International Consultants  

1.  Investment and structured trade finance and export credit insurance and guarantee 
experts—4 person-months (estimates). The technical assistance (TA) will require two international 
consultants with expertise in the following: 

(i)  medium- and long-term trade and investment insurance and guarantees provided by 
official (multilateral development banks, export credit agencies, and export import 
banks) and private insurers and guarantors; 
(ii)  project and structured trade finance; 
(iii)  Berne Union, Prague Club, and other insurance and guarantee organizations;  
(iv)  issues related to foreign direct investment and trade; 
(v)  Organisation  for  Economic  Co-operation  and  Development  (OECD)  pricing 
guidelines; 
(vi)  Asian Development Bank (ADB) and its products, including credit enhancement 
products; 
(vii)  syndication programs provided by multilateral development banks (e.g., B loans, 
reinsurance, guarantee-of-record); 
(viii)  sustainable development; 
(ix)  Asia and Pacific region; and  
(x)  training of government officials on the use of credit enhancement products. 

2.  The international consultants are expected to perform the following tasks: 

(i)  design  and  develop  training  materials  for  (a)  2.5  days  workshop  for  mid-level 
managers; and (b) half-day workshop for senior managers; 
(ii)  deliver the training; 
(iii)  coordinate  the  preparation  and  operation  of  the  workshops  with  the  national 
consultant and the ADB resource person; 
(iv)  prepare evaluation reports for each workshop; 
(v)  assess the evaluations provided by the participants; 
(vi)  provide recommendations on measures to be taken by ADB to strengthen the use of 
credit enhancement products (CEPs); and  
(vii)  prepare  a  final  report  summarizing  the  results  of  the  evaluations  and  provide 
recommendations on measures to be taken by ADB to strengthen the use of CEPs.  

B.  National Consultant 

3.  Research and project associate—4 person-months (estimates). The national consultant 
should have substantial experience in managing TA projects in Asia and 3–5 years of experience 
in one or more of the following areas: commercial cofinancing, risk mitigation instruments and 
providers,  and  project  and  structured  trade  finance.  Excellent  writing  abilities  and  strong 
quantitative and computer skills are required. The consultant will work at ADB headquarters during 
TA implementation. 

4.  Working under the supervision of  ADB Office of Cofinancing Operations staff and the 
international consultants, the national consultant will perform the following tasks: 

(i)  help the international consultants organize the briefings and workshops;

