(ii)  assist  in  preparing the training  program  curriculum, materials,  and  presentation 
papers; 
(iii)  assist ADB staff at headquarters and in resident missions in identifying developing 
member country (DMC) officials; 
(iv)  arrange  training  venue,  travel  of  resource  persons,  DMC  officials,  and 
reimbursement of expenses; 
(v)  help the international consultants prepare final reports; 
(vi)  develop a CEP blog for use in ADB, DMCs, and the private sector covering ADB 
credit enhancement products; and  
(vii)  perform other tasks as required by ADB Office of Cofinancing Operations staff and 
the international consultant.
